___NOTES___

Meta Pixel Tag by Up Blue — v1.2.0

Browser-side companion to "Meta Conversion API Tag by Up Blue" (sGTM).
Designed for deterministic deduplication via shared event_id.

v1.2.0 changes:
- fbq init + fbevents.js injection now runs BEFORE event skip logic, so the
  SDK starts downloading even for skipped events (session_start, scroll, etc.).
  This gives the browser Pixel a timing head start over CAPI, fixing the issue
  where PageView and ViewContent only appeared from "Server" in Events Manager.
- Added explicit fbq('consent', 'grant') call to match reference Pixel template
  behavior and prevent events from being blocked by external consent revocation.
- Removed 'gtm.dom' from GA4_TO_META_EVENT (page_view already maps to PageView).
- Added gtm.js, gtm.dom, gtm.load to ALWAYS_SKIP to prevent duplicate or
  custom-event fires from GTM internal events.

Key features:
- Same GA4→Meta event mapping as the CAPI tag
- Hardcoded skip list for GA4 events without Meta equivalent (same as CAPI tag)
- To track skipped events, use a separate tag instance with Manual mode
- Auto-reads ecommerce data from dataLayer (GA4 format)
- Built-in content_ids deduplication
- Conditional num_items (only InitiateCheckout/Purchase)
- Uses trackSingle/trackSingleCustom to avoid cross-pixel contamination
- Event ID as a first-class parameter for easy deduplication
- No Advanced Matching (handled by sGTM CAPI)
- No GDPR consent dropdown (uses GTM Consent Mode natively)
- Own agent string: upblue-GTM-WebPixel-1.0.0

Created by Up Blue (upblue.pl)


